intro:
The humanities and social sciences focus on subjects like economics, psychology, and history, while the humanities explore philosophy, languages and literature, and the arts. A degree in Humanities provides skills such as critical thinking, communication skills, logical reasoning, and analytical ability. SUB-DISCIPLINES  Development Studies Fine Arts Fashion Designing Mass Communication and Journalism Religion and Theology Those students who are interested in creativity can opt Arts stream. Moreover, the social science majors strengthen interpersonal communication, presentation, writing, and research abilities, leading them to succeed in the field. 

There are a plethora of career opportunities with a degree in the humanities and social science field. Depending on the majors and specializations within multidisciplinary disciplines, they can pursue a career in Communications, English, Geography, History, Journalism, Liberal Arts, Music, Philosophy, Political Science, Social Work, Sociology, Psychology, Writing, and so on.
